19- LCN: 2001302681
 
 Subki, Taqi al-Din 'Ali ibn 'Abd al-Kafi, al-Sayf 
al-maslul 'ala man sabba al-Rasul / tasnif Taqi al-Din 
'Ali ibn 'Abd al-Kafi al-Subki al-Shafi'i ; haqqaqahu 
'an nuskhat al-mu'allif wa-'allaqa 'alayhi wa-dhayyalahu 
Iyad Ahmad al-Ghawj. al-Tab'ah 1. 'Amman : Dar al-Fath, 
2000. $14.15 (U.S.). 666 p. : facsims. ; 25 cm. 
"Published for the first time, from five manuscripts, 
including one written by the author himself. The book is 
a study of the legal and theological rulings related to 
the station of the Prophet Muhammad (Allah bless him and 
give him peace). It contains important investigations in 
Islamic law, principles of jurisprudence, theology, and 
hadith sciences, and ends with a section on the 
character and traits of the Prophet"-- English t.p. 
Includes bibliographical references (p. 628-649) and 
indexes. Muhammad, Prophet, d. 632; cult; prophetic 
office; blasphemy (Islam); early works to 1800. Ghawj, 
Iyad Ahmad. 
 
 
